d 'XTMIXEDROOT': module to compute the fraction of nonstationary (unit-root) units in a mixed panel: the Ng (2008) estimator with Westerlund (2016) bias-adjusted fixed-T inference
d
d	xtmixedroot estimates theta, the fraction of units in a
d panel whose autoregressive representation contains a unit root,
d and	 tests H0: theta = theta_0 for any theta_0 in (0,1]. Unlike
d conventional panel unit-root tests, which only test the extreme  
d  hypotheses that all units are nonstationary or all are
d stationary, xtmixedroot quantifies how many units are
d nonstationary,    which is the quantity Pesaran (2012) recommends
d reporting alongside any panel unit-root test. 
d
d KW: panel data
d KW: unit roots
d KW: stationarity
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260713
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f xtmixedroot.ado
f xtmixedroot.sthlp
f xtmixedroot_methods.sthlp
f xtmixedroot_example.do
